GENESIS 2                                 GENESIS 2

Fonts:

I'm trying the "New Standard" font, because it looks slightly compact, but has
proper serifs. Download it from
    https://dl.static.1001fonts.net/niceid/n/e/new-standard.zip to your .fonts
directory like this ..
    
    cd ~/.fonts
    curl -O https://dl.static.1001fonts.net/niceid/n/e/new-standard.zip
    unzip new-standard.zip
    fc-cache .   # load into X


BUGS:
    Every chapter should have 3 lines at the bottom of the page.  Having a drop
    capital dangling into the margin is not great.  1 Peter 3:22 spacing
    Afrikaans extra blank line before drop caps We need better paragraph
    breaks.  Synchronisation of paragraphs should be preferred, but not forced. -
    FIXED: use needspace package

    
    Every new book should have 15% of the page at the bottom or something that
    looks good.

    Italics in KJV required.

    Table of contents

    First and last verse references in page header WORKAROUND ... used chapter title only

    Check that page headers make sense: we might need left/right to be stored in a variable and extract part of that 

    Afrikaans version capitalisation correction: GeseËNd

    Chosen font is not used - FIXED: don't use T1 fontenc package

    New chapters don't always align in Afrikaans and English

    Page headers seem to be the very last thing on the next page, or even worse, the first thing on the next page
